    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">This deck is made to race through your deck getting your fellowship beefed up as fast as possible. Also it sets up for a site 9 Balrog by using Gimli to throw it to the bottom of the deck as well as throwing a Power and Terror to the bottom. With 4 Goblin Sneaks you will have at least 4 goblins to use Power and Terror with. Always use your Goblin Sneaks to put a Goblin Runner or other cheap Goblin on the bottom of your deck. This deck is meant to use Archery through Aragorn, Legolas, Orophin and Rumil to kill your enemies minions than use Shoulder to Shoulder, Galadriel, Elrond and Choice of Luthien to heal every one involed. If any minions survive use Eomer or Aragorn to finish them off. Use Vilya and Athleas to remove any annoying conditions. The key to this deck is moving slowly while your minions go Balistic on your foe. When you reach site 7 your opponent will rarely be higher. Then use your maneuver phase healing to race to site 9. I doubt your opponent will have anything worse for you to face then what you have in store for them. Also if anyone can answer my question I would appreciate it: Can you Power and Terror the Balrog twice if you have two in your hand? </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
